<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,582,1075]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,762,787]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Magalhaes" box="[322,642,762,787]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" refString="Magalhaes, C. &amp; Turkay, M. (2010) A new freshwater crab of the genus Brasiliothelphusa from rio Aripuana, Southtern Amazon Region, Brazil (Decapoda: Psedothelphusidae). Nauplius, 18 (2), 103 - 108." type="journal article" year="2010">Magalhães &amp; Türkay (2010)</bibRefCitation>
originally assigned 
<taxonomicName box="[868,1087,763,787]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Melothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dardanelosensis">
<emphasis box="[868,1087,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">M. dardanelosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Magalhaes &amp; Turkay, 1986" authorityName="Magalhaes &amp; Turkay" authorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Brasiliothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1237,1436,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Brasiliothelphusa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Magalhaes" box="[151,469,798,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" refString="Magalhaes, C. &amp; Turkay, M. (1986) Brasiliothelphusa a new Brazilian freshwater-crab genus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Pseudothelphusidae). Senkenbergiana biologica, 66, 371 - 376." type="journal article" year="1986">Magalhães &amp; Türkay, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, on the basis of two single characteristics of the first gonopod, namely its enlarged apical plate and the open apical field of spines not bordered by two longitudinal crests along the surface of the gonopod. However, most morphological characters used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Magalhaes" box="[899,1251,870,895]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" refString="Magalhaes, C. &amp; Turkay, M. (1986) Brasiliothelphusa a new Brazilian freshwater-crab genus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Pseudothelphusidae). Senkenbergiana biologica, 66, 371 - 376." type="journal article" year="1986">Magalhães &amp; Türkay (1986)</bibRefCitation>
for the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[151,350,907,931]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Brasiliothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,350,907,931]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Brasiliothelphusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[377,427,907,931]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Magalhaes &amp; Turkay, 1986" authorityName="Magalhaes &amp; Turkay" authorityYear="1986" box="[545,1072,906,931]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Brasiliothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tapajoense">
<emphasis box="[545,709,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">B. tapajoense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Magalhaes" box="[729,1072,906,931]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" refString="Magalhaes, C. &amp; Turkay, M. (1986) Brasiliothelphusa a new Brazilian freshwater-crab genus (Crustacea: Decapoda: Pseudothelphusidae). Senkenbergiana biologica, 66, 371 - 376." type="journal article" year="1986">Magalhães &amp; Türkay, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) do not apply either to 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Melothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dardanelosensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">M. dardanelosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or to 
<taxonomicName box="[400,514,942,966]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Melothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiaka" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[400,514,942,966]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">M. apiaka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[522,586,942,967]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[522,580,942,967]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">n. sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Based on the characters of the first gonopod observed in the present study, 
<taxonomicName authority="Magalhaes &amp; Turkay, 2010" authorityName="Magalhaes &amp; Turkay" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,685,978,1003]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Melothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dardanelosensis">
<emphasis box="[151,364,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">B. dardanelosensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Magalhaes" box="[372,685,978,1003]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" refString="Magalhaes, C. &amp; Turkay, M. (2010) A new freshwater crab of the genus Brasiliothelphusa from rio Aripuana, Southtern Amazon Region, Brazil (Decapoda: Psedothelphusidae). Nauplius, 18 (2), 103 - 108." type="journal article" year="2010">Magalhães &amp; Türkay, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, can no longer be retained in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1138,1337,979,1003]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Brasiliothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1138,1337,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Brasiliothelphusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it is here transferred to the new genus 
<taxonomicName box="[546,712,1014,1038]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Melothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[546,712,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Melothelphusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<taxonomicName box="[762,982,1014,1038]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Melothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dardanelosensis" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[762,982,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">M. dardanelosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[992,1096,1014,1039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[992,1096,1014,1039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">n. comb.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Magalhaes" box="[1113,1425,1014,1039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" refString="Magalhaes, C. &amp; Turkay, M. (2010) A new freshwater crab of the genus Brasiliothelphusa from rio Aripuana, Southtern Amazon Region, Brazil (Decapoda: Psedothelphusidae). Nauplius, 18 (2), 103 - 108." type="journal article" year="2010">Magalhães &amp; Türkay,2010</bibRefCitation>
). The similarities and differences between 
<taxonomicName box="[611,830,1051,1075]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Melothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dardanelosensis" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[611,830,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">M. dardanelosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[836,939,1050,1075]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[836,939,1050,1075]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">n. comb.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[993,1107,1051,1075]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudothelphusidae" genus="Melothelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiaka" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[993,1107,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">M. apiaka</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1113,1176,1050,1075]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1113,1176,1050,1075]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are discussed below.
</paragraph>
